topics.title: Low Pass Filter
topics.description: A low pass filter is a type of analog electronic filter that allows low-frequency signals to pass through while blocking high-frequency signals.
evidence_quotes: Now a little bit after you've hit the cutoff point, the filter keeps reducing the amplitude by 20 decibels per decade.
For every time the frequency increases by a factor of 10, the amplitude decays by a factor of 10.
